WEBVTT

00:01:19.125 --> 00:01:20.500
Doctor...

00:01:20.833 --> 00:01:27.333
they are writing all these articles about
cocaine hubs and drug smuggling in this area.

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:29.708
Do you believe it?

00:01:31.416 --> 00:01:33.166
It's not that I don't believe it.

00:01:35.291 --> 00:01:39.291
I have been getting hints
every now and then.

00:01:42.083 --> 00:01:44.416
Some of them have come to
me for prescription drugs.

00:01:45.708 --> 00:01:52.375
Those who are cocaine addicts can't
hide their addiction from a doctor.

00:01:53.583 --> 00:01:56.583
Ok, so they are doing drugs.

00:01:56.666 --> 00:01:59.500
But why the murders?

00:01:59.875 --> 00:02:02.500
They are very closely related.

00:02:02.541 --> 00:02:03.916
For example...

00:02:04.125 --> 00:02:05.833
Suppose, I am a cocaine dealer...

00:02:06.166 --> 00:02:09.708
And you have found out
about my business...

00:02:09.916 --> 00:02:15.416
In such a situation, will it be wise for me
to keep you alive?

00:02:15.541 --> 00:02:17.208
You might go tell the police, right?

00:02:17.250 --> 00:02:20.041
And land me at jail?

00:02:20.875 --> 00:02:24.666
Even then, do you think I'll
keep you alive?

00:02:27.333 --> 00:02:32.500
Looks like you have really understood the
the thought process of criminals very minutely.

00:02:33.375 --> 00:02:39.083
See, Mr. Ajit, It's a good deed
to give a home to a homeless...

00:02:39.625 --> 00:02:42.500
But, I have warned you that
tears of strangers are only water...

00:02:42.541 --> 00:02:45.958
No no. I do not believe that Mr. Atul
has done this.

00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:49.208
It'll be decided after
the court's verdict...

00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:51.041
But...

00:02:51.041 --> 00:02:52.041
See, Doctor...

00:02:52.416 --> 00:02:54.332
He is a young man, looking for a job.

00:02:54.333 --> 00:02:55.707
He has no place to take shelter.

00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:57.083
My room is pretty big...

00:02:58.125 --> 00:02:59.957
That's why I had agreed to
stay with him.

00:02:59.958 --> 00:03:03.833
But the man is never at home, isn't it?

00:03:03.916 --> 00:03:07.291
Do you know what kind of job he had?

00:03:07.416 --> 00:03:09.416
What would he do! The problems
of being unemployed.

00:03:09.583 --> 00:03:11.833
He used to wake up and leave to
hunt for a job.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:15.333
The entire day he used to go here and
there... Asking around in offices.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.958
You do know what the situation with
jobs are like here.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:21.434
At night, maybe he used to go looking
for a job as a night guard.

00:03:21.458 --> 00:03:23.375
These are very dark times.

00:03:28.333 --> 00:03:30.124
Atul Babu, you're here?

00:03:30.125 --> 00:03:31.125
Weren't you arrested?

00:03:31.208 --> 00:03:34.458
A cop is deadlier than a tiger...

00:03:35.416 --> 00:03:38.458
What happened Ghanashyam!
Oh, Ghanashyam! Wait!

00:03:40.291 --> 00:03:43.582
Atul Babu, you are back?
The police let you go?

00:03:43.583 --> 00:03:44.666
Yes, Doctor.

00:03:45.125 --> 00:03:46.833
There's a proverb in English, isn't it?

00:03:47.583 --> 00:03:48.791
"Bad Penny"

00:03:52.250 --> 00:03:54.750
Even I came back as rejected.

00:03:55.833 --> 00:03:57.207
Even the police did not take me.

00:03:57.208 --> 00:03:59.416
No, it's actually good
that you've come back.

00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:00.874
That is very good.

00:04:00.875 --> 00:04:03.375
But for me... you know...

00:04:03.958 --> 00:04:05.874
No no. Absolutely, I understand.

00:04:05.875 --> 00:04:07.165
I hope you understand.

00:04:07.166 --> 00:04:07.875
It's true.

00:04:07.876 --> 00:04:12.708
You might get involved in aiding and abetting
case, if you give shelter to a criminal like me.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:17.290
So, do I need to vacate by tonight?

00:04:17.291 --> 00:04:20.083
No no. You can stay tonight.

00:04:20.958 --> 00:04:23.208
But, tomorrow morning
you will have to...

00:04:24.291 --> 00:04:27.791
All right. Thank you, Doctor.

00:04:37.333 --> 00:04:38.708
Ajit!

00:04:39.916 --> 00:04:41.083
Call Mr. Anukul!

00:04:41.916 --> 00:04:44.083
This is the problem with
these locks, understand?

00:04:44.291 --> 00:04:46.291
It just cannot be fixed
once there is a problem.

00:04:46.416 --> 00:04:50.416
Here take it. I'll call the carpenter
tomorrow and get it fixed, ok?

00:04:50.708 --> 00:04:52.083
All right, Doctor.

00:05:10.958 --> 00:05:12.333
Come in.

00:05:18.125 --> 00:05:19.500
Doctor...

00:05:19.583 --> 00:05:22.500
I have come to test the
benefits of your medicines.

00:05:22.875 --> 00:05:25.625
I have a splitting headache.
Can you give me anything?

00:05:25.666 --> 00:05:27.041
Yes, sure.

00:05:27.541 --> 00:05:32.875
You have a headache because of you
haven't eaten anything, understood?

00:05:32.916 --> 00:05:37.707
Here, have this. You will be
fine by tomorrow morning.

00:05:37.708 --> 00:05:38.583
All right.

00:05:38.584 --> 00:05:43.958
Mr. Ajit... You don't look too
well either.

00:05:44.083 --> 00:05:48.875
You look weak after all the excitement.
Your body is giving up, is it?

00:05:50.458 --> 00:05:51.833
Wait.

00:05:54.125 --> 00:05:55.791
You...

00:05:56.750 --> 00:05:59.041
take this.

00:05:59.208 --> 00:06:02.583
You take this. You will feel
a lot better tomorrow morning.

00:06:05.541 --> 00:06:08.083
All right, Doctor.
We'll take leave.

00:06:08.125 --> 00:06:09.500
Namoshkar!

00:06:15.708 --> 00:06:18.332
Doctor, have you heard of anyone named
Byomkesh Bakshi?

00:06:18.333 --> 00:06:20.832
No. Who is he?

00:06:20.833 --> 00:06:22.833
Even I do not know.

00:06:23.250 --> 00:06:25.375
I heard his name at the police station.

00:06:26.125 --> 00:06:28.457
He's the one who is
investigating this murder.

00:06:28.458 --> 00:06:29.458
Doctor...

00:06:32.583 --> 00:06:34.083
Bye. Good night.

00:06:52.083 --> 00:06:54.375
Hey! What is the matter!

00:06:55.333 --> 00:06:58.500
Stay a little longer in this darkness...

00:06:59.666 --> 00:07:01.708
light will illuminate from here itself.

00:07:02.333 --> 00:07:03.791
But... light?

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:05.375
You mean...

00:07:05.458 --> 00:07:08.207
Light will come from the
source of darkness?

00:07:08.208 --> 00:07:10.250
That itself is your light!

00:07:10.875 --> 00:07:12.040
That's good.

00:07:12.041 --> 00:07:13.916
For now, let there be darkness.

00:08:09.416 --> 00:08:11.416
It's a very sad story, Doctor...

00:08:12.083 --> 00:08:15.333
A professional like you, stabbing a pillow?

00:08:16.750 --> 00:08:19.125
Don't move! Don't you dare move!
Ajit! Ajit!

00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:22.750
Take the knife from his hand.

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:10.750
What?

00:09:11.416 --> 00:09:12.915
What is my crime?

00:09:12.916 --> 00:09:15.000
There's more than one, Doctor.

00:09:15.458 --> 00:09:16.833
Cocaine business..

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:18.875
Murder...

00:09:19.083 --> 00:09:24.082
Do you have any proof that
I have a cocaine business?

00:09:24.083 --> 00:09:26.124
Yes, sure I do.

00:09:26.125 --> 00:09:28.833
Your medicine boxes from abroad...

00:09:29.041 --> 00:09:30.500
Am I wrong?

00:09:31.708 --> 00:09:33.000
Tell me something, Doctor.

00:09:33.666 --> 00:09:36.666
What medicine did you
give us tonight?

00:09:37.166 --> 00:09:39.458
Morphine. Isn't that right?

00:09:40.583 --> 00:09:44.665
The charge sheet for your crimes is being
prepared at the police station.

00:09:44.666 --> 00:09:46.875
But for now...

00:09:47.208 --> 00:09:52.666
I arrest you for attempting to murder
Byomkesh Bakshi.

00:09:52.750 --> 00:09:54.750
Inspector, do you have
a matchbox?

00:10:06.041 --> 00:10:10.665
No matter how dried garlic may get...
It never loses its flavor.

00:10:10.666 --> 00:10:13.750
Remember Mr. Detective.

00:10:18.666 --> 00:10:21.416
Thank you. Thank you, Mr. Ajit.

00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:27.833
Satyanweshi?????

00:11:31.958 --> 00:11:34.625
You know.. I don't like the sound
of the term "Detective"...

00:11:35.375 --> 00:11:37.708
and "investigator" is even worse.

00:11:37.958 --> 00:11:40.249
That's why I've given myself the name...

00:11:40.250 --> 00:11:41.375
"Truth Seeker"

00:11:42.250 --> 00:11:44.000
Come in... come in.

00:11:44.125 --> 00:11:46.583
Welcome! Welcome to the house
of the poor.

00:11:46.625 --> 00:11:48.208
Hey Putiram!

00:11:48.333 --> 00:11:50.373
Get a cup of hot tea and
some kachoris (Flatbread).

00:11:55.916 --> 00:11:57.333
Your house looks very nice!

00:11:58.875 --> 00:12:01.875
- So I take it that you live alone.
- Yes, Putiram being my sole companion.

00:12:03.208 --> 00:12:05.416
Ajit, didn't you say you were a writer?

00:12:06.791 --> 00:12:08.040
Is that your professional calling?

00:12:08.041 --> 00:12:11.416
How could I resist the urge
to make a profession out of my passion?

00:12:12.125 --> 00:12:15.166
The interest on my inheritance
is enough for a bachelor's life like mine.

00:12:16.416 --> 00:12:20.958
Hence, I have embraced celibacy
and devoted me to a literary life.

00:12:22.291 --> 00:12:24.290
Now that I know where you
live, I will take my leave!

00:12:24.291 --> 00:12:26.333
Wait! I just sent Putiram
to bring hot kachoris.

00:12:26.625 --> 00:12:29.666
That can wait, it's already
very late now. Goodbye.

00:12:29.791 --> 00:12:33.624
Listen Ajit, after what's happened
in that house,

00:12:33.625 --> 00:12:35.425
I don't think you will
be able to live there.

00:12:35.833 --> 00:12:38.416
Why don't you move in here?
This house isn't so bad after all.

00:12:40.666 --> 00:12:43.707
- Are you returning the favor?
- Haha, not exactly a favor.

00:12:43.708 --> 00:12:47.708
I have a feeling I will be
needing you more from now on.

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:49.800
Enjoying your company
has become a bad habit!

00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:52.708
- I have one condition.
- Tell me.

00:12:52.875 --> 00:12:55.708
I want to take all the mysterious
incidents and cases that you solve,

00:12:55.916 --> 00:13:00.750
add a little color to them
and publish them as fiction. Agree?

00:13:01.666 --> 00:13:02.833
Hmm...

00:13:06.333 --> 00:13:10.124
Look, I don't really see any
reason to object to this.

00:13:10.125 --> 00:13:14.790
And as you know very well,
the desire for popularity...

00:13:14.791 --> 00:13:17.625
is indomitable.

00:13:22.583 --> 00:13:24.375
- You don't say!
- But I am.

00:13:26.583 --> 00:13:29.499
Hey, where are you rushing off to again?

00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:33.165
Let me bring my belongings!
- Okay, don't forget to bring mine!

00:13:33.166 --> 00:13:35.249
I won't. I will be back for
lunch in the afternoon!

00:13:35.250 --> 00:13:37.791
Okay, see you soon!

00:14:40.958 --> 00:14:43.791
Nomoshkaar! (Goodbye)

00:14:45.416 --> 00:14:49.208
- Babu, have you thrown away the faulty
pins kept at the back of the shop?

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:50.250
No, why?

00:14:54.041 --> 00:14:55.708
I can't find them anywhere.

00:14:55.750 --> 00:14:58.583
Good riddance, it was rubbish anyway.

00:15:07.333 --> 00:15:10.082
Gramophone pin! Yet again!

00:15:10.083 --> 00:15:13.374
Gramophone pin murders continue!

00:15:13.375 --> 00:15:15.041
Gramphone pin! Yet again!

00:15:15.208 --> 00:15:17.458
The strange murders using
gramophone pins continue!

00:15:23.416 --> 00:15:23.666
Breaking and fresh news regarding
the gramophone pin murders!

00:15:23.667 --> 00:15:27.207
Breaking and fresh news regarding
the gramophone pin murders!

00:15:27.208 --> 00:15:30.375
Read them in the papers! Take! Read
about the gramophone pin killings!

00:15:51.833 --> 00:15:54.708
Byomkesh! Again!

00:15:58.541 --> 00:16:00.500
Are you listening to me? LISTEN!

00:16:00.625 --> 00:16:02.582
Another murder by a gramophone pin.

00:16:02.583 --> 00:16:06.499
"Readers may be aware that a few days ago,
Jaihari Sanyal was walking when

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:08.333
he suddenly fell to his own death.

00:16:08.416 --> 00:16:12.833
We surmised then that a massive
conspiracy may be lurking behind this.

00:16:12.875 --> 00:16:15.541
That suspicion has now been confirmed.

00:16:16.083 --> 00:16:19.083
With the incidence of another
ghastly murder yesterday.

00:16:19.125 --> 00:16:23.500
Last evening, famous and wealthy
businessman, Kailash Chandra Moulick...

00:16:27.833 --> 00:16:30.833
It is clear that it is not a mere accident.

00:16:31.125 --> 00:16:34.375
A group of sinister barbaric murderers
has taken over the entire city.

00:16:34.416 --> 00:16:36.832
It is difficult to ascertain
their identities or their motive.

00:16:36.833 --> 00:16:41.249
What is strange, is there
weapon and modus operandi-

00:16:41.250 --> 00:16:45.458
Give me the advertisement page for a bit. - You want
to read the ads when there's a murderer on the loose?

00:16:46.583 --> 00:16:48.915
Have you noticed an interesting ad
in the papers for the last few days?

00:16:48.916 --> 00:16:50.556
I don't really follow the advertisements.

00:16:51.250 --> 00:16:54.207
You don't read the ads in newsppaers?
Then what do you read?

00:16:54.208 --> 00:16:56.540
What the newspapers are meant for. News.

00:16:56.541 --> 00:17:02.082
Who cut his finger in Manchuria and who delivered
triplets in Brazil, this is what you read?

00:17:02.083 --> 00:17:07.625
Listen Ajit, if you want real news,
start reading the ad section.

00:17:08.125 --> 00:17:11.957
Oh really? The reporters
these days must be very sly.

00:17:11.958 --> 00:17:17.207
Instead of publishing more advertisements,
they are wasting pages on this gibberish.

00:17:17.208 --> 00:17:21.041
If they can't satisfy people like you,
they won't be selling their papers anyway.

00:17:21.250 --> 00:17:24.958
-Oh really?
-The real news is in the ad pages.

00:17:27.166 --> 00:17:29.083
All that is happening in the country,

00:17:30.208 --> 00:17:34.041
who's selling what in order to
rob people in broad daylight,

00:17:35.666 --> 00:17:39.500
or who is planning to
smuggle stolen goods, -

00:17:41.208 --> 00:17:44.875
news like these appears only in
the ad section. Like this one.

00:17:50.916 --> 00:17:53.624
"Thorns on the Road"
If you want to rid the road of thorns,

00:17:53.625 --> 00:17:56.957
at 5:30 PM on Saturday,
wait at Dharmatala Tram Depot...

00:17:56.958 --> 00:18:02.375
by the lamp post next to the tram
line on the southwest end.

00:18:02.916 --> 00:18:06.165
This ad has been appearing every
Friday for the last three months.

00:18:06.166 --> 00:18:08.832
But..what is the point
of this cryptic message?

00:18:08.833 --> 00:18:10.791
There has to be some reason

00:18:11.625 --> 00:18:15.458
No one spends so much on
ads without any reason.

00:18:16.791 --> 00:18:20.916
However Mr.Writer, one thing
is clear from all this.

00:18:22.000 --> 00:18:25.750
What is that?
- His insistence on anonymity.

00:18:26.791 --> 00:18:32.208
Whoever he is, he wishes to call
the shots from behind the scene.

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:37.791
I am not sure I follow you.

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:41.958
Let's assume you have a thorn on your path, and
you want to get rid of it. What do you do?

00:18:42.708 --> 00:18:45.915
You stand at the specified spot and
wait, holding the lamp post.

00:18:45.916 --> 00:18:50.540
You go and wait by the lamp post
like an idiot for half an hour

00:18:50.541 --> 00:18:55.375
but nobody appears with the noble aim
of eliminating your thorns for you

00:18:56.166 --> 00:18:59.006
You get irritated and give up,
thinking the entire matter is just a ruse

00:18:59.041 --> 00:19:00.041
At that precise moment...

00:19:05.166 --> 00:19:10.874
And that's how a relationship based on transaction
is established between the two of you

00:19:10.875 --> 00:19:14.083
But his identity, and how he looks...

00:19:15.333 --> 00:19:16.875
You know nothing of it.

00:19:34.500 --> 00:19:36.583
No Byomkesh, your theory
sounds preposterous.

00:19:37.291 --> 00:19:41.000
Disbelieving whatever is beyond your comprehension
only reveals your own weakness, Ajit.

00:19:42.125 --> 00:19:43.125
Very well, tomorrow is a Saturday.

00:19:43.126 --> 00:19:45.000
There isn't much work in the evening

00:19:45.416 --> 00:19:46.875
I will prove it to you then.

00:19:48.708 --> 00:19:49.708
How exactly?

00:19:55.958 --> 00:19:57.000
Putiram!

00:20:00.375 --> 00:20:05.291
Old... plump... and stout...

00:20:07.416 --> 00:20:11.250
With a walking stick in hand,
expecting to meet us...

00:20:12.625 --> 00:20:14.945
Because there's no one living on
the third floor except us.

00:20:18.083 --> 00:20:19.083
Come in!

00:20:28.125 --> 00:20:32.500
Which amongst you is
Detective Byomkesh Bakshi?

00:20:33.458 --> 00:20:35.416
That would be me...

00:20:36.125 --> 00:20:37.375
But I am no detective.

00:20:38.125 --> 00:20:39.208
I prefer "Truth-Seeker".

00:20:40.416 --> 00:20:44.083
Why don't you make yourself comfortable? Then
we can listen to your gramophone pin mystery.

00:20:47.291 --> 00:20:49.416
H...how on earth did you know?

00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:52.375
Just a guess.

00:20:53.541 --> 00:20:54.708
First of all, your age...

00:20:56.041 --> 00:20:57.875
Secondly, you look well off,

00:20:59.125 --> 00:21:02.416
Thirdly, you are in some trouble which
has brought you to our doorstep.

00:21:04.333 --> 00:21:07.582
I-I...

00:21:07.583 --> 00:21:10.708
was looking for you because I mean...

00:21:12.458 --> 00:21:13.958
I was thinking of you

00:21:15.125 --> 00:21:17.085
Now I am convinced I have
come to the right place.

00:21:17.708 --> 00:21:20.249
Mr. Byomkesh, you alone can save me!

00:21:20.250 --> 00:21:22.708
I expect nothing from the
police, they are useless!

00:21:24.416 --> 00:21:26.999
Can you imagine, in broad daylight.

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:29.582
there have been five murders already!

00:21:29.583 --> 00:21:31.623
I was almost on the verge
of getting killed me!

00:21:31.666 --> 00:21:35.415
Tell me everything from the start
without keeping anything back.

00:21:35.416 --> 00:21:37.957
I am Ashutosh Mitra.

00:21:37.958 --> 00:21:40.708
I live nearby, at Lebutala.

00:21:41.458 --> 00:21:47.291
I have been traveling a lot for
business, ever since I was 18

00:21:47.625 --> 00:21:50.708
which left me with very little
opportunity to settle down.

00:21:51.875 --> 00:21:55.708
However, I was not really
interested in marriage anyway

00:21:57.125 --> 00:22:03.000
I am essentially very self-contained.
I like living by myself...

00:22:04.416 --> 00:22:11.375
However, it has been two years
since I retired from work.

00:22:12.208 --> 00:22:14.915
All my life earnings,

00:22:14.916 --> 00:22:21.082
say around 1.5 lakhs have
been deposited in the bank.

00:22:21.083 --> 00:22:23.958
That is all I have, that is what I live on.

00:22:25.541 --> 00:22:27.707
Besides this, I-I...

00:22:27.708 --> 00:22:31.500
am fond of listening to music

00:22:33.125 --> 00:22:35.666
This is how I passed my time,
life was peacefully passing me by

00:22:36.083 --> 00:22:37.250
Anyone living with you?

00:22:39.625 --> 00:22:43.958
No relatives as such except
for a nuisance of a nephew

00:22:44.666 --> 00:22:48.000
who comes by often to ask
for monetary allowances.

00:22:48.583 --> 00:22:54.208
Mr. Byomkesh, I cannot tolerate these
the spendthrift and alcoholic gamblers at all!

00:22:54.416 --> 00:22:55.541
What does this nephew do?

00:22:56.791 --> 00:23:02.207
I don't let that scoundrel in my house!

00:23:02.208 --> 00:23:03.583
Where does he live?

00:23:04.375 --> 00:23:09.041
He is now in lockup, the police have
arrested him on counts of public drinking

00:23:09.583 --> 00:23:13.708
