00:50:45.458 --> 00:50:47.208
I am very fond of this bicycle...

00:50:48.833 --> 00:50:51.125
Will you make sure it is somewhere safe?

00:50:53.708 --> 00:50:56.708
Where do you think you are going, Ajit?

00:50:58.250 --> 00:50:59.850
Do you know what sort
of bicycle that is?

00:51:00.666 --> 00:51:04.000
That bell houses all the gramophone pins.

00:51:04.083 --> 00:51:06.763
Be patient, why can't you wait
quietly? The police are on their way.

00:51:07.708 --> 00:51:11.958
You are very clever, Mr. Byomkesh! - Thank
you but you are no less, Mr. Prafulla.

00:51:12.750 --> 00:51:15.416
Not everybody can make such
an ingenious fatal machine.

00:51:15.958 --> 00:51:17.875
I am from Midnapore.

00:51:18.083 --> 00:51:19.833
My father owned a cycle shop...

00:51:20.166 --> 00:51:21.958
That's where I learned how to repair them...

00:51:22.375 --> 00:51:30.375
I lost him, my brothers, everything...
to the flood.

00:51:31.791 --> 00:51:33.458
I came look for work in the city...

00:51:34.750 --> 00:51:36.625
But work...

00:51:39.083 --> 00:51:40.708
To avoid dying of starvation....

00:51:41.958 --> 00:51:44.125
this strange business idea struck me...

00:51:45.375 --> 00:51:47.541
I have removed the thorns
for a great many people...

00:51:50.416 --> 00:51:51.536
What else could I have done?

00:51:53.250 --> 00:51:54.833
We all need to sustain our own selves.

00:51:56.250 --> 00:51:57.333
Don't you agree?

00:52:00.916 --> 00:52:04.250
Could I get some..some water?

00:52:05.875 --> 00:52:07.625
My throat feels parched...

00:52:08.333 --> 00:52:10.000
You will get some at the station.

00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:16.041
Then, can you give a
paan from my container?

00:52:17.458 --> 00:52:18.958
Just to soothe my throat a bit.

00:52:30.750 --> 00:52:31.750
Thank you.

00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:35.958
You can take one each as well.

00:52:38.875 --> 00:52:39.875
Keep it back!

00:52:47.625 --> 00:52:49.208
So you won't let me go then?

00:52:51.291 --> 00:52:52.666
You'll hand me over to the police?

00:52:56.750 --> 00:52:57.750
Mr. Byomkesh-

00:52:59.791 --> 00:53:01.791
Even clever men make mistakes...

00:53:02.125 --> 00:53:05.708
You can never hand me over to the police-
- Ajit! Ajit! AJIT!

00:53:06.208 --> 00:53:10.957
Ajit! Hold him still! Mr. Prafulla?!

00:53:10.958 --> 00:53:14.916
Had you eaten the paan too,
we could have gone away together...

00:53:19.666 --> 00:53:22.166
What is going on? Is he dead?

00:53:37.375 --> 00:53:39.041
The culprit has escaped justice, Officer.

00:54:08.666 --> 00:54:09.750
Byomkesh-

00:54:10.833 --> 00:54:15.458
How did you know that the man behind the thorns ad
and the gramophone pin killer was one and the same?

00:54:19.708 --> 00:54:21.333
What is the thorns ad really saying?

00:54:22.375 --> 00:54:26.541
If you have to obliterate those who
stand in the way of your happiness...

00:54:27.291 --> 00:54:29.125
they can avail of his services.

00:54:29.750 --> 00:54:32.916
On the other hand, all the victims
of the gramophone pin killer...

00:54:33.250 --> 00:54:35.666
they were all thorns on
somebody's road to happiness.

00:54:37.000 --> 00:54:38.375
And they were all heirless.

00:54:38.875 --> 00:54:44.000
All their wealth would go to
some nephew, or sons-in-law...

00:54:45.333 --> 00:54:49.875
The greed for inheritance is pretty evident
from Mr. Ashutosh's case itself.

00:54:50.500 --> 00:54:51.780
This is just one side of things.

00:54:52.625 --> 00:54:56.166
The other thing deals with
these ads in the newspapers...

00:54:57.083 --> 00:55:01.625
where living thorns are eliminated
with a weapon that looks like a thorn.

00:55:01.958 --> 00:55:03.208
A guess again?

00:55:04.333 --> 00:55:05.416
This was an easy guess.

00:55:10.250 --> 00:55:11.333
Let's go...

00:55:12.208 --> 00:55:14.875
We can deposit Mr. Ashutosh
cheque reward in the bank.

00:55:15.541 --> 00:55:21.208
And return the cycle bell, in exchange
for your bounty from the police. Let's go.

00:55:22.083 --> 00:55:23.923
Do you know what I was
thinking instead, Ajit?

00:55:25.083 --> 00:55:29.291
If they let me keep the bell instead
of the two thousand rupees...

00:55:30.625 --> 00:55:34.666
I mean it's strange and marvelous
piece of craftsmanship...

00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:38.083
Yet, what a waste...

00:55:39.041 --> 00:55:40.083
Byomkesh-

00:55:40.791 --> 00:55:43.552
You have been reading news of
all that's going on around the world...

00:55:43.916 --> 00:55:48.958
If a simpleton from the village can
create something this impactful...

00:55:50.125 --> 00:55:55.540
if the superpowers of the world combine their
resources and brains to fight each other

00:55:55.541 --> 00:55:57.958
can you imagine where the
world is headed towards?

00:56:00.958 --> 00:56:01.958
Yes, I can imagine...

00:56:03.083 --> 00:56:07.208
Perhaps an invention which can annihilate
an entire city within moments...

00:56:08.875 --> 00:56:10.875
Will you applaud its craftsmanship as well?

00:56:11.875 --> 00:56:14.666
No, I would say that it's destructive.

00:56:15.208 --> 00:56:17.250
But one thing, Ajit....

00:56:17.875 --> 00:56:21.416
I hate the criminal mentality
of a skilled man...

00:56:22.333 --> 00:56:24.083
but I still respect his mind.

00:56:26.166 --> 00:56:31.166
Let's go return the bell and get
the money as decided... Come.